<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Version 2.3.0 Copyright issue! <p>
Most (maybe all) non-player thunderlords in the game use fire, not thunder; this is most obvious during the thunderlord quest. This is a leftover from the dragonrider copyright issue, where dragonriders were turned into thunderlords and were supposed to be using lightning-based attacks from now on. 
</p>
<p>
Renaming them firelords won't please a certain copyright-holder... )-; 
</p>
<p>
The fix would be to turn fire breath into lightning type effects taken from the same code as for players, or even lightning breath if one doesn't care it doesn't work like the thunderlord-player ability. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: Actually, I didn't intend them to use lightning when I renamed them.   I was just hurriedly removing all the remaining Pern-ish one night (Because I was tired of them, not because we were being forced to. The forced renaming was already done.)  I don't see that they have to use lightning, either; thunder refers to a sound, not necessarily the sound from lightning. 
</p>
<p>
If we did make them use lightning that would make the game much harder, because lightning immunity is rarer. 
</p>
<p>
Simon: a lightning spell, cast not too frequently, might do the trick (the danger level of the quest is 80 if I recall, it deserves a little special). Or couldn't we turn this around and player thunderlords get to choose which breath they have on character creation? 
</p>
<p>
Or we can stick with the NPC-player inconsistency. 
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


